# This file describes installing Jenkins in Ubuntu 14.04 server.

1. Download Jenkins repository key to a file say "jenkins.key"
   $ wget -q -O - http://pkg.jenkins-ci.org/debian/jenkins-ci.org.key
   
2. Add the key
   $ sudo apt-key add jenkins.key
   OK

3. Add the Jenkins repo to sources file in apt
   $ sudo sh -c 'echo deb http://pkg.jenkins-ci.org/debian binary/ > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list'
   
4. Update 
   $ sudo apt-get update

5. Install Jenkins
   $ sudo apt-get install jenkins
   
Jenkins will automatically start.

Access its UI from URL:
   http://jenkins_server_ip:8080
